<setup>
    <selectFromSequence name="a" from="-1" to="1" step="2"/>
    <selectFromSequence name="b" from="-2" to="2" step="2"/>
    <selectFromSequence name="c" from="-2" to="2" step="2" exclude="$b -1*($b)"/>  

    <function symbolic="false" name="f">$a*x + $b*sin(x) + $c*cos(x)</function>
    <derivative name="fP">$f</derivative>
    <derivative name="fPP">$fP</derivative>
</setup>  

<p>
  Let <m>f(x) = <math simplify>$f</math></m>.
</p>  

<p>
  <ol marker="a.">
    <li>
      <p>Determine the following derivative formulas: </p>        
      <p><m>f'(x)=</m><answer>$fP</answer></p>
      <p><m>f''(x)=</m><answer>$fPP</answer></p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>Determine a value of <m>x</m> such that <m>0 \lt x \lt 2\pi</m> and the tangent line to <m>y = f(x)</m> is horizontal there</m>.  If there are no such values, enter <q>none</q>. </p>
      <p><m>x = </m><mathInput name="crnum"/>
        <answer>
        <award><when>
          (0 < $crnum < 2*pi) and $$fP($crnum) = 0
        </when></award>
      </answer></p>  
<!--      <p>crnum = $crnum, <m>f'($crnum) = $$fP($crnum) </m> </p> -->
    </li>     
    <li>
      <p>Determine a value of <m>x</m> such that <m>0 \lt x \lt 2\pi</m> and <m>f''(x)</m> changes sign at that <m>x</m>-value.  If there are no such values, enter <q>none</q>. </p>
      <p><m>x = </m><mathInput name="poi"/>
        <answer>
        <award><when>
          (0 < $poi< 2*pi) and $$fPP($poi) = 0
        </when></award>
      </answer></p>  
    </li>  
    
  </ol>  
</p> 